<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Avis Europe Aims for Asian Expansion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Avis Europe, the European car
rental group, is seeking to expand its presence in Asian markets
over the next year despite the region's serious economic troubles.
</P>
<P>
Alun Cathcart, chairman of Avis Europe, was quoted by
Thursday's Financial Times as saying, "We are currently
unrepresented in Japan, China and India and it is my main
preoccupation that we should get a foothold in those markets."
</P>
<P>
Cathcart noted that Avis would seek licensees in South Korea
and India as a way of entering those markets, but could
conceivably take an equity stake in a Japanese operation.
</P>
<P>
Announcing its interim results Wednesday, Avis Europe said its
existing Asian operations, all of which are through licensees,
generated income of 800,000 pounds (about 1.3 million U.S.
dollars), down 12 percent on the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Explaining the group's interests in Asia, Avis Europe, which is
well-managed and deserves its market rating, made it clear that
even if Europe's economic recovery were snuffed out, it could
still adjust fleet capacity quickly to cope. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
