<HEADLINE> Ethiopia: About 25,000 Ethiopians Repatriated </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia announced
Thursday that a total of 24,970 Ethiopians have been expelled
from Eritrea since the border dispute between the two countries
erupted in early May, this year.
</P>
<P>
The announcement was made after some 4,000 Ethiopians were
repatriated from Eritrea recently.
</P>
<P>
The Office of Government Spokeswoman Selome Taddesse quoted
the figures released by the local Disaster Prevention and
Preparedness Commission as saying that those people were
expelled through the border at Zalambessa, Adwa, Bure and
Djibouti.
</P>
<P>
The office said in a press release, "Until now there has been
only one reception center near the Bure border at Logiya where
4,000 people have already sought refuge. Yesterday a new center
was opened at Mile and 1,000 people arrived straight away.
Another 500 are expected to arrive there today." 
</P>
</TEXT>
