Thursday the international community to find a political solution
to the Kosovo problem, saying that Athens was doubtful about the
effectiveness of a military intervention.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference, Greek government spokesman
Dimitris Reppas said that Greece continued to have reservations
about the possibility of a strike by international forces on
Kosovo and would continue to urge a political resolution to the
problem.
</P>
