because the U.N. Security Council had not decided on the matter.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, the U.N. Security Council demanded an immediate
cease-fire and negotiations to end the conflict in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) issued Thursday
an activation warning for a limited air strike and a phased air
campaign in the Yugoslav province of Kosovo, where ethnic
Albanians made up 90 percent of its nearly 2 million population
and have been demanding independence from Belgrade. 
