<HEADLINE> Britain Pledges to Encourage Africa's Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Britain would help
build prosperity in Africa, and richer Africa was in the interest
of the rest of the world, Britain said here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the Second U.N. Security Council Ministerial
Meeting on Africa, Robin Cook, Britain's secretary of states of
foreign ans commonwealth affairs, said Britain would promote
African trade by demanding that African countries get a fair deal
in international trade negotiations and that Africa benefit from
the global economy.
</P>
<P>
Cook said Britain would reduce African debt, so that African
economies were not crippled by having to pay extravagant
proportions of their income to countries far richer than them.
</P>
<P>
Britain would promote African development by refocusing its
development assistance so that it would make a real difference to
the poorest people and get through to the rural areas which had
got a small minority of aid, Cook said
</P>
<P>
Cook said his country would also encourage sound economic
management in African countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
