JERUSALEM -- A bomb exploded at a Jerusalem bus stop during
rush hours Thursday morning, injuring an Israeli soldier and
wrecking the stop's shelter.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police said the explosive device, weighing about one
kilogram and possibly triggered by a timer, went off at about
8:00 am (local time) near the campus of the Hebrew University,
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli soldier sitting at the bus stop was lightly hurt in
the head when the bomb went off, the police said.
(Israel-Bomb)
</P>
