- - - -
</P>
<P>
AMMAN -- Jordanian new government Thursday won the vote of
confidence in the Lower House of Parliament, Jordan's official
PETRA news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Of the 80-member House, 64 deputies voted in favor of the
23-member new cabinet, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
With the vote of confidence, the House members hoped that the
government will live up to its promises outlined in the policy
statement to combat corruption, unemployment and poverty.
(Jordan-New Cabinet)
