<HEADLINE> Air Services to Resume in Tanzania's Mbeya Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Air services in Tanzania's
southwest region of Mbeya which stopped two decades ago are expected
to resume by the end of next month.
</P>
<P>
The services which were cut off following the collapse of the then
East African Community (EAC), are going to be provided by the
Arusha-based Precision Air Limited and Air Malawi, reports from Mbeya
said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
General manager of Precision Air, Philemon Kisamo, at a function to
introduce his company in Mbeya on Tuesday, said their chartered planes
will operate between Mbeya-Iringa-Dar es Salaam and Arusha, with two
flights a week. An aircraft is able to carry up to 48 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Air Malawi has declared it will introduce services
between Mbeya region and Malawi using its 12-seater aircraft twice a
week by the end of next month. 
</P>
