<HEADLINE> China Grateful to People Expressing Condolences on Death </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- China said Friday it is
grateful to people around the world who have expressed condolences
over the death of former Chinese president Yang Shangkun.
</P>
<P>
To this regard, the Communist Party of China (CPC), the
National People's Congress (NPC), the State Council, the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and the Central
Military Commission made a joint announcement through their top
executive bodies.
</P>
<P>
Yang died in Beijing on September 14 at age of 92.
</P>
<P>
Since then, said the announcement, China has received messages
of condolences from many foreign heads of state and government,
leaders of parliaments, political parties and international
organizations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, similar messages have also come in from foreign
ambassadors in China, friendly groups, people from all walks of
life, and Chinese compatriots from Hong Kong, Macau and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
"We are authorized to express our heartfelt thanks to those
people for their expression of condolences," said the announcement
issued by the general offices of the CPC Central Committee, the
NPC Standing Committee, the State Council, the CPPCC National
Committee and the Central Military Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
