<DOCNO> XIE19980925.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Primakov Urges Fight Against Shadow Economy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Russia's newly-appointed Prime
Minister Yevgeny Primakov Friday emphasized the importance to
fight against "shadow economy" in creating a market economy in
Russia, the Itar-Tass news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a meeting of the Interior Ministry collegium,
Primakov said, "Whether we can build a market economy of a
civilized type, break negative tendencies in business, change the
mentality of businessmen, distorted over the past years by crime,
depends on whether we are able to achieve an improvement in
fighting the shadow economy and economic crime."
</P>
<P>
The scope of the shadow economy in Russia surpasses 40 percent
of gross domestic product, according to the Interior Ministry of
Russia.
</P>
<P>
Primakov noted the Interior Ministry must make efforts to
support the anti-crisis measures of the government and the
president.
</P>
<P>
He meanwhile spelled out measures for consolidation of the
banking system, the ruble's stabilization, state monopoly on
alcohol.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the premier also said the Interior Ministry
must toughly oppose separatist tendencies, which are the most
tangible in times of the economic hardships. 
</P>
</TEXT>
