<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK's Education to Bring Up Youth Capable of Taking New </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The ultimate aim of the
education in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) is
to bring up youth capable of taking challenges of the 21st
Century, a leading official of the SAR Education Department said
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference for the launching of the
"Synergy in the 21st Century -- Information Technology (IT) in
Education" project, Anthony Tong Kai-hong, Senior Assistant
Director of Education Department, said the competitiveness of Hong
Kong is confronted with tough challenges as the SAR approaches to
the new millennium.
</P>
<P>
The toughest challenge to the SAR's education is that the local
teachers have to keep abreast of latest knowledge and information
in a rapidly changing time so that youth can be brought up to take
the challenges of the new century, he said.
</P>
<P>
He recalled that SAR's Chief Executive Tung Chee Hwa had
stressed in his first Policy Address that Hong Kong should aspire
to be a leader in the information world of tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
To realize this, an ambitious five-year strategy had been
launched, which will, among others, incorporate IT elements in the
school curriculum and enhance the provision of technology in a
more structured framework. The target is to support teaching of 25
percent of the curriculum through IT by the year 2002, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jointly launched by the Education Department and local
organization The Lions Club of Metropolitan Hong Kong, the
"Synergy in the 21st Century -- IT in Education" project
encourages local teachers to apply more IT in education so as to
raise the standard of students.
</P>
<P>
There are two elements in the Project -- setting up of an
education software reference bank and IT in Education Excellency
Award. 
</P>
</TEXT>
