<HEADLINE> China Introduces Bond Information Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The China Bond Information
Network, the country's first Internet website offering information
on bond trading, entered operations today.
</P>
<P>
China has issued over 900 billion yuan in bonds over the past
few years. Some types of bonds are traded on the Shenzhen and
Shanghai stock exchanges, according to official sources. They also
noted that the interbank market for bond trading has also expanded
rapidly.
</P>
<P>
The network was initiated by the Central Bonds Registration and
Settlements Corporation of China and Beijing Hexun Information
Science and Technology Co. Limited.
</P>
<P>
The website will offer information related to bond varieties,
market trends and related laws and regulations. 
