<HEADLINE> Supreme Court Urges Further Judiciary Restructuring </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China plans to strengthen
internal restructing of the judiciary in order to ensure justice,
eradicate corruption and enhance efficiency, according to Xiao
Yang, president of the Supreme People's Court.
</P>
<P>
The new central government was seated in March this year and
shortly thereafter instituted the Education and Restructuring
Campaign in response to criticism raised by deputies to the
National People's Congress (NPC). Courts at the provincial,
prefectural and county levels have thus far recouped
misappropriated funds of over 8.27 million yuan (one million US
dollars).
</P>
<P>
The numbers of verdicts rendered during the second quarter of
this year jumped by 14.35 percent on figures for the first quarter
of the year.
</P>
<P>
Xiao said the judiciary must refrain from resorting to
complacency in light of the notable achievements.
</P>
<P>
"Further strengthening the judiciary remains as a long-term
task," said Xiao, noting that civil, economic and lower level
people's courts will be the focal points of the ongoing campaign
</P>
<P>
"Courts which failed to introduce concrete measures during the
initial campaign will be required to do so in the future and all
illegal trial procedure will be subject to investigation," said
Xiao, adding that "actions arousing public dissent will be
thoroughly examined and individuals responsible will be subject to
appropriate punishment."
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court plans to introduce a number of new
measures to strengthen internal supervision, including inviting
NPC deputies, members of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and well-known public figures
to serve as special representatives to table both grievances and
proposals.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court plans to establish a liaison office
which will assist NPC deputies and facilitate their efforts to
supervise the work of judges.
</P>
<P>
Lower courts will establish special departments and assign
staffers responsibility for liaison work with people's congresses
on the same level.
</P>
<P>
Xiao added that documents, reports and other material issued
by courts should be submitted to assist the NPC in properly
supervising the judiciary.
</P>
<P>
The Supreme People's Court and lower courts have introduced
strengthened regulations governing internal supervision.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
