<HEADLINE> Nanning Mounts Wild Animal Protection Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Nanning, capital of south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, today launched a
campaign to collect 10,000 signatures on a petition designed to
promote the protection of wild animals.
</P>
<P>
The campaign, initiated by the provincial and Nanning forestry
bureaus, is designed to increase general public awareness of the
need to protect wild animals.
</P>
<P>
Guangxi is home to 884 wild animals species, with many species
under state protection, including white-headed leaf
monkeys, and both black-necked and long-tail pheasants.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, the People's Congress of the Guangxi
Zhuang Autonomous Region has passed a number of regulations
governing the protection of wild animals.  
