<HEADLINE> China's First On-line Hotel Reservation Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- "Visit our website and you
can instantly book a room in any of the hotels listed," the China
Business Alliance Hotel Reservation Network said today, as China
opened its first hotel reservation system on the Internet.
</P>
<P>
CBAnet, sponsored by the State Information Center and Beijing's
SiTech Group, enables people to book a reservation in over 300
hotels in more than 50 cities via computer.
</P>
<P>
Detailed information about the hotels is available on the
Internet, with pictures of the rooms.
</P>
<P>
CBAnet offers a wide range of choices, room rates, and
locations, and people who use the electronic room reservation
system can enjoy a 30 to 60 percent discount.
</P>
<P>
CBAnet started trial operations in June and has already helped
more than 15,000 people arrange their trips. The network will
expand its coverage to 500 hotels in 100 cities by the end of this
year. 
</P>
