<HEADLINE> Chinese Seminar On Urban Agriculture Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A two-day seminar on urban
agriculture, sponsored by the China Agricultural Society and the
Jiusan (September 3) Society, opened today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Agronomists will discuss future development of this special
form of agriculture, which involves high-profit agriculture in
areas around large and medium-sized cities that provides produce
and entertainment for urbanites.
</P>
<P>
Although urban agriculture has maintained rapid growth in the
past few years, it still lags far behind other urban development,
according to a member of the China Agricultural Society, who says
that poor transport facilities in suburban areas hinder
development.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said, the central government needs to develop
measures to limit the blind expansion of large cities and to
provide related policies for the growth of urban agriculture.
 
</P>
