<HEADLINE> State Council Holds Executive Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Premier Zhu Rongji today
chaired the Eighth Executive Meeting of the State Council, the
Chinese cabinet.
</P>
<P>
The Draft Law on Administrative Reconsideration was approved in
principle at the meeting. The law is based on the previous
experience with the Regulations on Administrative Reconsideration
adopted in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the new law is to correct illegal and irregular
administrative activities and protect the interests of
Chinese citizens, legal entities and institutions.
</P>
<P>
The draft will be revised and submitted to the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress for approval.
</P>
<P>
Today's meeting ended with the approval of several documents,
including Mangement Regulations for the Registration of Social
Groups, Provisional Management Regulations for Registration of
Nongovernmental Institutions and Provisional Management
Regulations for the Registration of Government Institutions.
