<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-25 11:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Shows off Military Force amid Tension with </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Amid tension with the Afghan
Taliban militia, Iran on Friday showed off its military force by
displaying three newly-developed medium-range Shahab-3 (Meteror-3)
missiles in a military parade here.
</P>
<P>
Decorated with colors, the three giant missiles came at the
end of the military parade held in the Azadi (Freedom) Square on
the occasion of the Defense Week to mark the eight-year war
between Iran and Iraq from 1980 to 1988.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time for Iran to show the Shahab-3 missile
with a range of 1,300 kilometers, which was successfully tested on
July 22 and provided Iran with a new deterrent force.
</P>
<P>
Iranian President Mohammad Khatami said at the parade ceremony
that Iran should build up powerful armed forces to defend the
country's sovereignty and territorial integrity, particularly the
eastern border following the latest development in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
"The Iranian government pursues a policy of tension-reducing,"
Khatami said, but the policy should be supported by the strong
armed forces, including the army, the Islamic Revolutionary Guards
Corps (IRGC), the security and the Basij (volunteers) forces.
</P>
<P>
He strongly condemned the Taliban's crimes of massacre of
innocent people, particularly the killing of eight Iranian
diplomats and a reporter early last month in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Praising the armed forces for their devotion to the country
and the Islamic revolution during the eight years of the
Iran-Iraq war, the Iranian president said Iran's future will
surely be better than today, with the support of the armed
forces.
</P>
<P>
To show their capability to defend the country, the Iranian
armed forces held military parades simultaneously throughout the
country, with the biggest one held in Mashhad, Khorasan province
which borders Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Following the killing of the Iranians by the Taliban in
northern Afghanistan, the IRGC has deployed 70,000 troops and the
army built up 200,000 forces along the 850-kilometer border with
Afghanistan and announced their readiness to carry out any order
to take revenge on the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
Despite of heavy pressure for military action against the
Taliban, the moderate government of President Khatami expressed
hope that the issue with the Taliban could be solved through
peaceful means, though it reiterated that Tehran reserves the
right to take any measure to defend the country and rights of its
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
