<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets French Prime Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji
Thursday expressed China's desire to expand bilateral cooperation
with France in line with the spirit enshrined in last year's joint
statement.
</P>
<P>
Zhu told his French counterpart Lionel Jospin that China has
always attached great importance to relations with France. The two
leaders joined in an afternoon meeting in Beijing's Great Hall of
the People. Jospin arrived in Beijing earlier in the day to begin
an official three-day visit.
</P>
<P>
Zhu extended a warm welcome to Jospin and expressed great
appreciation for his counterpart's efforts to promote bilateral
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
China and France are permanent members of the UN Security
Council, and shoulder heavy responsibility for world affairs, said
Zhu, adding that both nations treasure national independence,
pursue independent foreign policies, advocate multipolarization
and share similar or identical views on many important
international issues.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that establishing a comprehensive partnership
oriented to the 21st century will not only conform to the basic
interests of the two nations, but will also greatly benefit world
peace, stability and development.
</P>
<P>
He said bilateral relations have progressed smoothly since
their April meeting in Paris. He added that the momentum of
high-level contacts has been maintained, and noted that
substantial results have been achieved in terms of economic, trade
and agricultural cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two countries maintained extensive contacts in the
scientific, technological, cultural and educational spheres, and
implementation of relevant cooperative projects and exchange
programs has proceeded smoothly. Zhu said the two nations have
continuously reinforced coordination and cooperation in the realm
of international affairs.
</P>
<P>
Relations between China and France continue to advance along
the correct track, and China is ready and willing to further
promote the momentum of sound development, said Zhu.
</P>
</TEXT>
