<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Air quality was relatively
good in China's major cities for the past week, but the air quality
dropped slightly in some northern cities, according to the China
Environmental Monitoring Center.
</P>
<P>
The center's lastest air-quality report shows the cities of
Beijing, Tianjin, Urumqi, Taiyuan, Zhengzhou, Guangzhou and 5
others suffered from slight air pollution on September 18-24.
</P>
<P>
The major problem in Beijing and Guangzhou was nitrogen
oxide. The 9 others suffered from suspended particles.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the temperature varied greatly day and night in
northern China over the past week, and the wind speed was slow, so
that it did not disperse the pollutants in air.
</P>
<P>
The cities of Chongqing, Shanghai, Kunming, Hangzhou, Guilin,
Shenzhen, and 23 others reported good air quality.
</P>
<P>
The cities of Yantai, Shantou, Haikou, Xiamen, Ningbo and
Beihai all enjoyed excellent air quality during the
period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
