<HEADLINE> Ethiopia to Export Marble to Middle East </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopia has
successed in meeting over 80 percent of local marble demand and
is planning to export the products to Middle East countries,
according to the Ethiopian Herald on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dagnew Gideon, General Manager of The Ethiopian Marble
Industry, told press that the industry is planning to export the
product to countries like Yemen and Saudi Arabia where they are
said to be in high demand.
</P>
<P>
He said that the industry has increased its output at the
Gulale, Nefas Silk and Bole factories for domestic use.
</P>
<P>
Gideon said that last year the industry planned to produce
3,700 cubic meters of marble blocks for the processing factories
and succeeded in supplying over 4,147 cubic meters for
construction purpose.
</P>
<P>
He added that the industry last year earned over 14.7 million
Birr (2.1 million US Dollars) by producing and supplying over
46,000 cubic meters of marble blocks.  
</P>
