<HEADLINE> Share Prices Slide on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Share prices gyrated from
positive to negative territory on the Singapore Stock Market
Friday after its rise of almost 50 points over the past three
days.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) slipped by 8.06 points
to end at 923.92 points in line with weak regional sentiment
following an overnight sharp tumble on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover was 119.66 million units worth 135.87
million Singapore dollars (about 79.41 million U.S. dollars).
Losers led gainers by 165 to 55 with 200 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Heshe took the lead in the trading volume of the day as it had
a turnover of 12.62 million stocks traded. It was followed by ST
Engg that had 7.48 million units done. KepLand was next with 7.20
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Auric Pac led the increase of the day as it gained 25 cents to
close at 1.00 Singapore dollar. SIA F went up 15 cents to finish
at 9.05 Singapore dollars. Thai Pr edged up 15 cents to end at
2.46 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SPH was the biggest loser of the day as it
lost 20 cents to close at 13.80 Singapore dollars. Sp Ld slid by
17 cents to finish at 2.50 Singapore dollars. NatElec shed off 16
cents to end at 3.64 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that the market kept nose toward lower from the
start of trading as profit-taking added to early pressure on the
market after Thursday's surge on expectation of a U.S. interest
rate cut.
</P>
<P>
They also said the market index managed to recoup most of its
losses in late dealings on selected buying of blue chips by
foreign institutional funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
