<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Two border security force
(BSF) personnel were killed and another seriously injured when a
powerful bomb exploded inside a temporary picket in Baramulla
district in Indian-held north Kashmir Friday.
</P>
<P>
The bomb was suspected to have been planted by militants inside
the picket on the top floor of a local bank, a BSF spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
