<HEADLINE> Nigeria Recovers Money From Former Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian Head of State General
Abdulsalam Abubakar confirmed that his government has recovered a
substantial amount of money from the family of former leader,
late General Sani Abacha.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar made the disclosure Thursday at a question-and-answer
program on the Cable News Network (CNN). He stressed that
efforts were still being made "to see what we can recover."
</P>
<P>
Abubakar, who took office in June following the sudden death
of General Abacha, had been under pressure to investigate his
predecessor, who had allegedly stolen billions of U.S. Dollars
from the country's huge oil income and kept them in foreign
banks.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar confirmed for the first time that his government was
investigating Abacha in early September, when he addressed his
first world press conference in Abuja, capital of Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
According to him, the investigation has received positive
cooperation from foreign governments. 
</P>
