<HEADLINE> 760 Kilograms of Cocaine Seized in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- A total of 760 kilograms of
pure cocaine were seized by Turkish anti-narcotics police squads
Thursday in a freighter off the coast near the southern Turkish
port city of Mersin, the leading daily Milliyet reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A police patrol boat intercepted the ship for search and found
the narcotics in a container, the largest haul in the last few
years, a police spokesman was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen suspects including three foreign nationals were taken
into custody, he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the U.S. anti-narcotics authorities had been
following the ship sailing from Chile to Europe and informed the
Turkish police of the possible shipment of drugs on the ship.
</P>
<P>
According to him, four companies including a U.S. firm were
involved in the incident and most of the drugs are prepared to be
transported to Europe except a small part of sales in Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long been used by Turkish and foreign drug dealers
as a springboard to smuggle narcotics from southeastern Asian
countries to European markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
