<HEADLINE> 25 Killed in India's Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- At least 25 people, most of
them school children, were killed and 28 others seriously injured
when a rail engine rammed into a state road transport corporation
bus at an unmanned level crossing near Bothalapalem village in
Andhra Pradesh of South India Friday.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said that the majority of the 65
passengers in the bus were school children bound for Miriyalguda
town for the tenth class supplementary exam. The mishap occurred
when the speeding engine of a goods train hit the rear portion of
the bus.
</P>
<P>
