<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With French Prime Minister (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin,
who is currently on an inspection tour of this capital city of
east China's Anhui Province, met with visiting French Prime
Minister Lionel Jospin today.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his appreciations of the fact that Jospin
attaches importance to Sino-French relations since he resumed the
prime minister's post and voiced his conviction that Jospin's
current China trip would push forward bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
China and France enjoy a longstanding relationship, Jiang said,
adding that the leaders of both countries have maintained frequent
contacts with each other in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang pointed to his visit to France in 1994 and French
President Hirac's China trip in May last year, when the two heads
of states signed Sino-French Joint Statement, pledging that the
two countries would establish a comprehensive partnership oriented
to the next century.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the current international situation is
undergoing profound changes and that peace and development remain
the main trends of the times. The tendency of a multi-polarized
world is turning increasingly obvious with the international
situation becoming more relaxed, he acknowledged.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, Jiang added, unstable and uncertain factors still
exist and the old world political and economic order, which is
unjust and irrational, remains basically unchanged. He added that
the process of a globalized world economy is accelerating,
bringing about both opportunities and risks.
</P>
<P>
Under these circumstances, China and France should have all the
reasons to enhance consultation, expand common ground and increase
cooperation from a historic and strategic point of view, so as to
contribute to the setting up of a just and rational international
political and economic order in the next century, Jiang said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980925.0158 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With French Prime Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang also briefed the French visitors on China's domestic
situation and the work of post-flood rehabilitation in the flooded
areas.
</P>
<P>
He told Jospin that China's flood control has won an all-round
victory and the people are going all out with the rehabilitation
work in the flood-hit regions.
</P>
<P>
The flood fighting drive has eloquently demonstrated the unity
of the Chinese army and people and their indomitable spirit and
heroism, as well as the cohesion of the Chinese nation, Jiang
noted.
</P>
<P>
Jospin said his meeting with President Jiang in Anhui is of a
special significance, which help acquaint himself with the efforts
of local people to fight flood and develop economy.
</P>
<P>
China's resolve to carry out reform and opening up to the
outside world remains unshakable despite the impact of Asian
financial crisis and the devastating flooding in the country this
year, Jospin said, adding that he had highest esteem for this
resolve.
</P>
<P>
The French prime minister also admired China's great
changes. China has constantly advance its social progress while
maintaining its political stability, and this represents the most
efficient growth mode, Jospin said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jospin said, France values its ties with China,
adding that his current China tour is aimed at furthering the
comprehensive partnership between the two countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
