<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Turkish newspapers Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom)
</P>
<P>
-- Alaattin Cakici, a notorious Turkish mafia boss, was
sentenced to six months' imprisonment by a French court Thursday
for entering the country with a false diplomatic passport.
</P>
<P>
Cakici was arrested in the French city of Nice last
month. Turkish police has been demanding his extradition because
of criminal charges against him and his alleged relations with
some politicians.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning)
</P>
<P>
-- Istanbul Mayor Tayip Erdogan said at a press conference
Thursday that the 10-month prison sentence would not stop him
from continuing his political career, terming the conviction "a
wrong decision."
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Supreme Court of Appeals Wednesday upheld the
sentence rendered by the State Security Court in Diyarbakir in
April on the grounds that the pro-Islamic politician "incited
hatred based on religious differences" in a speech last year.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National)
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish police seized Thursday morning a total of 760
kilograms of pure cocaine near the southern city of
Mersin. Fourteen suspects including three foreign nationals were
arrested in the raid.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has long been used as a springboard by drug dealers to
traffick narcotics from some Asian countries to European
markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
