<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Developing Information, Finance, And Technology Sectors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai's Mayor Xu Kuangdi
says that the city will give priority to the information, finance,
and technology sectors in the years to come and make information
technology a leading source of revenue by early next century.
</P>
<P>
Xu told the '98 Pacific Rim Forum, sponsored by the China
Council for Promotion of International Trade's Shanghai Branch
with help from Dragon World Co. Ltd. of Australia, earlier this
week that Shanghai will catch up with moderately developed
countries in per capita GDP and will become an international
economic, finance, and trade center by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
It plans to encourage more overseas banks to start opening
branches in the city and to give overseas financial organizations
wider access to Chinese currency business and to start offshore
financial services, he says.
</P>
<P>
The city will also make a great effort to expand the capital
market and standardize the money market to ensure healthy and
rapid development of the financial sector. It will also
concentrate on high-tech information, pharmaceutical, and new
materials industries by increasing cooperation with overseas
companies.
</P>
<P>
For the past several years, the city has been improving
infrastructure, increasing spending on environmental protection
and afforestation, speeding up rebuilding of old city areas, and
building more new residential quarters to make it a more
attractive place for investors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
