<HEADLINE> Lawmakers Meeting On Tourism Vs. Environment to Be Held in Guilin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Asian and Pacific
Parliamentarians' Conference on Environment and Development will
be held in Guilin, the capital of south China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region, on October 14.
</P>
<P>
Lu Congmin, deputy secretary-general of China's National
People's Congress Standing Committee, said here today that
lawmakers from 35 countries will discuss environmental protection
and natural resources and developing the tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, is expected to
meet with participants, and Zou Jiahua, vice-chairman of the NPC
Standing Committee, will preside over the opening ceremony, Lu
said.
</P>
