<HEADLINE> Kenya Beefs up Security Along Border with Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government has
strengthened security along the border with Uganda following a
fierce fight between Ugandan troops and rebels in eastern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The heavy exchange of gunfire between the Ugandan government
troops and the rebel Lords Resistance Army, took place earlier
this month seven kilometers away from the Kenyan-Ugandan border,
the East African Standard newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Thus it caused panic on the Kenyan side in the Mt. Elgon
district, sending Kenya's security on alert, said the report.
</P>
<P>
The Mt. Elgon District Security Committee has ordered
surveillance and patrols in border posts to phase off the area
from the run-away rebels.
</P>
<P>
Mt. Elgon District Commissioner John Munguti said Thursday
that his men were on the lookout to ensure Kenya's territory is
not used by the rebels.
</P>
<P>
"We have beefed up security and surveillance along the common
border to ensure that no run-away suspected armed rebels gain
entry in the area," he said. 
