<HEADLINE> Australia Leads Uzbekistan 2-0 in Davis Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Australia won the first two
singles with ease in Townsville on Friday, leading the best of
five series against Uzbekistan in the Davis Cup World Cup
qualifying.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Open champion Patrick Rafter won the first singles by
beating 254th-ranked Oleg Ogorodov 6-3, 6-3, 6-4 in front of a
capacity crowd of 4,900 at the Townsville Entertainment Center,
while teammate Jason Stoltenberg was rarely troubled in nipping
239th-ranked Vadim Kutsenko 7-5, 6-1, 6-0 in the second singles.
</P>
<P>
By winning the two singles, Australia is on its way to
celebrate as its doubles pair of Todd Woodbridge and Mark
Woodforde is odds-on to beat Ogorodov and Dmitri Tomashevich on
Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Rafter who won his second successive U.S. title, was tested in
the opening set by the strong backhand of Ogorodov as both
players exchanged breaks for 2-2.
</P>
<P>
Since then, Rafter found his rhythm in the serve-and-volley
game to break again for a 3-2 lead and sealed the first set in 43
minutes with a string of ground strokes.
</P>
<P>
After winning the first set, Rafter kept his top form to
collect the second set in 30 minutes and to break the seventh
game in the third set before signalling his victory for the home
crowd. 
</P>
