<HEADLINE> Tibet Begins Computer Education For Youth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 25 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Tibet
Autonomous Region has launched a computer education project, with
the first group of 41 computers earmarked for the use by local
teenagers.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Municipal Science and Technology Committee, the
Beijing Municipal Science and Technology Association, and Teenager
Computer World Magazine also donated 500 computer magazines to
help the region develop computer education among the young.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Tibet Autonomous Regional Science and
Technology Committee said the equipment and books and magazines
will be used mainly by teachers and students majoring in computer
technology.
</P>
<P>
The Computer Education Project For Teenagers, launched by the
China Science and Technology Commission, aims to encourage
scientific research institutes, schools and individuals in China's
developed areas to donate hardware and software, teaching
equipment, and computer books and magazines for the development of
computer education in western China.
</P>
<P>
Beijing Municipal Science and Technology Committee officials
said they hope to develop long-term computer-education cooperation
with the autonomous region. 
</P>
