the stalled negotiations as the reasons for the cancellations.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, it is now clear there will not be enough time
for teams to fill their rosters, go through a necessary period of
conditioning, and be ready to play preseason games by mid-Oc
tober," said NBA deputy commissioner Russ Granik.
</P>
<P>
NBA commissioner David Stern and Granik met with Players
Association executive director Billy Hunter and union president
Patrick Ewing for a brief session on Wednesday. It marked the
first time since August 6 that discussions were held. But both
sides refused to divulge the content of the meeting and no future
session was scheduled.
</P>
<P>
The cancellation comes on the heels of the league postponing
its referee trianing camp and rookie transition program. The
regeree training camp was scheduled to begin September 25, while
the rookie transition program was set for September 20-23.
</P>
<P>
The sides currently are awaiting a grievance ruling from
arbitrator John Feerick. The NBA Player Association filed a
salary grievance hours before the owners imposed a lockout on
July 1. 
