<HEADLINE> Factory Head Fined For Embezzlement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The head of a factory in
east China's Zhejiang Province must pay fines of 2.38 million yuan
(about 287,000 U.S. Dollars) for embezzling public property and
poor performance on duty.
</P>
<P>
In late 1991, Yi Lihua was the head of a collectively run
chemical fiber plant in the city of Shaoxing. During his tenure he
obtained materials and products and sold them to relatives and
friends at very low prices, sometimes even below cost.
</P>
<P>
Under his leadership, the factory borrowed funds from persons
and other enterprises at unreasonable high interest rates which
drove the factory to the edge of bankruptcy.
</P>
<P>
Local media disclosed that Yi took more than 430,000 yuan from
the factory in the name of bonuses and built luxurious villas in
his hometown.
</P>
<P>
Yi is the first factory head in the province to be fined for
such activities. Local officials explained that the amount of the
fine was worked out in accordance with relevant laws and
regulations.  
</P>
</TEXT>
