<HEADLINE> Private Economy Growing In Southwestern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The private economy has been
expanding fast in southwest China's Sichuan Province, where there
are more than 1.6 million private businesses employing about 2.14
million people.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, a great number of them are
profitable enterprises that have earned a good reputation around
the country.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, the province's private businesses, with a
a total registered capital of 7.54 billion yuan (about 908 million
U.S. Dollars), had an increase of 30.5 percent in total output
value compared with the figure for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The fast growth in the private sector has helped social and
economic development, and expanded the application of scientific
and technological developments in Sichuan, while contributing to
local revenue, one local official says. 
