<HEADLINE> Hurricane Georges Sweeps Across Cuba </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Hurricane "Georges" continued
its stormy route across the Caribbean on Thursday as it swept
across Cuba's eastern provinces of Guantanamo and Holguin, with no
reports of casualties.
</P>
<P>
The Meteorology Institute of Cuba said the hurricane's eye was
in Cuchillas de Toa, Guantanamo, some 650 miles east of Havana, at
21:00 local time on Thursday (0100 GMT Friday).
</P>
<P>
Chief meteorologist Jose Rubiera said Georges' center was 31
miles in diameter with a zone of calm in its eye, where there is
not a single drop of rain.
</P>
<P>
Outside the eye, however, heavy rains lashed down on towns and
villages as the hurricane moved west-northwest over Guantanamo and
Holguin at 13.75 miles per hour (mph), down from 73.75 mph when it
first entered Cuba.
</P>
<P>
According to forecasts, Georges will reach Camaguey and Ciego
de Avila in eastern Cuba and the central province of Sancti
Spiritus by early Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
Under an emergency measure of the Cuban National Civil Defense,
more than 20,000 residents have been evacuated as well as some
1,000 foreign tourists vacationing in areas along the hurricane's
route. 
</P>
</TEXT>
