<HEADLINE> China Suggests for Change of Home-and-Away Matches </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Football
Association (CFA) suggested their 2000 Olympics preliminary round
rivals to change the home-and-away matches to the double
round-robin formation, CFA officials said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
CFA has sent letters to its counterparts of Group 7, which
brackets Vietnam, the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and
Myanmar, saying China is willing to host one of the double round
if other FAs agree the suggestion.
</P>
<P>
It will be a big cost financially and physically, and give
lots of troubles to the domestic leagues, if the matches are to
be played on the home-any-away basis, CFA advised in the letters.
</P>
<P>
Besides, China also proposed to play the matches in May and
June, shortening the period from four months to two. The matches
were originally scheduled to start in February.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Football Confederation has no fixed rules indicating
how to play the preliminary round matches.
</P>
<P>
No responses have been received yet by now. 
</P>
</TEXT>
