<HEADLINE> Libyan Gunboat Fires on Italian Fishing Boat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A Libyan gunship rammed and
fired on an Italian fishing boat 30 nautical miles off the Libyan
coast Thursday morning, killing a Sicilian fisherman.
</P>
<P>
The boat's owner said the fishermen jumped overboard when the
boat caught fire and one drowned. The nine survivors were picked
up by other Italian fishing boats in the area.
</P>
<P>
The attack occurred about 2 a.m. local time when the gunboat
rammed and opened fire on the boat Orchidea which was carrying six
Sicilian and four Tunisian fishermen.
</P>
<P>
Italy immediately protested to the Libyan authorities and
demanded an explanation, the Italian Foreign Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said Libya expressed its regret over the
incident. Libya said its navy was never ordered to use weapons on
foreign fishing boats. Libya would investigate the case and
stressed its intent to avoid any repeat of the attack, the Foreign
Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred amid a dispute over fishing rights in the
Sicilian Strait involving Italy, Libya and Tunisia. 
</P>
