The Australian Financial Review:
</P>
<P>
-- Kim Beazley, leader of the Australian Labor Party, the
opposition, locked himself into another ambitious target Thursday,
promising to deliver 500,000 jobs in his first term as the
employment issue took center stage in the election campaign.
