<HEADLINE> Argentine International Reserves Drop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's total
international reserves dropped by 1.31 billion U.S. dollars in the
last 40 days, the financial newspaper Cronista reported on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
But it said the drop in the reserves was not a threat to the
country's banking system, because the net capital flight only
affected 300 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The remaining one billion dollars were still in the country,
the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
Argentina's international reserves now amount to 32.7 billion
dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
