<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Hotel Starts Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 25 (Xinhua) -- The renowned five-star
Beijing Hotel will take on a new look when the current
reconstruction and expansion of its major buildings are completed.
</P>
<P>
Geng Shizhong, the hotel's general manager, said the first
phase of renovation will be completed by the year of 2000.
</P>
<P>
The two buildings located at the western and middle parts of
the hotel will be rebuilt first, and the new building in the rear
will be expanded as well.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Hotel first opened in 1900, and many of its
facilities are now outdated and need to be refreshed, Geng said.
</P>
<P>
The second phase of reconstruction of the eastern building
will begin as soon as the first phase is completed.
</P>
<P>
The entire project is expected to cost around 700 million yuan
(around 84 million U.S. dollars).  
</P>
</TEXT>
