<HEADLINE> Spain Takes on Sweden in Davis Cup Semi-final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A strong Spanish team is
to clash with Davis Cup superpower Sweden away here this weeken
in a World Group semi-final.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish team, spearheaded by fifth-ranked Carlos Moya and
seventh-ranked Alex Corretja, will meet Sweden's 13-ranked Jonas
Bjorkman and 22-ranked Thomas Johansson.
</P>
<P>
Though the Spaniards' world rankings are well ahead of the
Swidish, six-times Davis Cup trophy winners Sweden, with their
crowd support, may turn those computer standings on their heads.
</P>
<P>
Friday's second singles will pit French Open champion Moya
against Swedish Davis debutant Johansson while Alex Corretja
meets challenge from Jonas Bjorkman in the first singles.
</P>
<P>
The experienced Swedes Bjorkman and Nicklas Kulti will take on
Spain's untested pairing of veteran Javier Sanchez and Julian
Alonso in Saturday's doubles.
</P>
<P>
Reverse singles on Sunday will feature Bjorkman against Moya
followed by Johansson and Corretja.
</P>
<P>
"I feel perfect," said Moya. "Everything is against us, but
we're hoping to get through."
</P>
<P>
Swedish players said that the indoor carpet was speeding up
just to their liking.
</P>
<P>
"It's got a low bounce, and that will help us against Spain,"
said Bjorkman, "We're all very happy with it.
</P>
<P>
Spain's best Davis Cup showings saw them reach the final in
1965 and 1967. 
</P>
</TEXT>
