<HEADLINE> Chile Reports Growth in Its Investments Abroad </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Chile's investments abroad
reached 2.583 billion U.S. dollars in the first eight months of
this year, more than 500 million dollars above the 2.067 billion
dollars in 1997, official reports said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The United States received the largest share of Chile's
investments, with 1.544 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Bank of Chile, 531 million dollars
went to South America, of which more than 383 million went to
Argentina alone.
</P>
<P>
Chile's investments abroad include financial establishments,
insurance, real estate, and services. 
</P>
</TEXT>
