<HEADLINE> Peru Set to Earn One Billion Tourist Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Peru is expected to earn one
billion U.S. dollars from tourism in 1998, Industry, Tourism and
Integration Minister Gustavo Caillaux announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
More than 800,000 tourists arrived in Peru in the last 12
months, said Caillaux, adding that an estimated number of one
million foreign tourists would visit the country in the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
The minister attributed the increase to economic reforms in
Peru, including the liberalization of the air transportation
sector. 
</P>
