<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-25 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NBA to Cancel Part of Preseason Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The NBA plans to cancel
at least some preseason games, Deputy Commissioner Russ Granik
said Thursday as the league's lockout and stalemate began its
13th week.
</P>
<P>
It will be the first time in the league's five decades that
either a preseason game or a regular season game invloving two
NBA teams has been cancelled because of labor problems.
</P>
<P>
Sources throughout the league said yesterday that they
expected the NBA to decide to cancel the entire preseason by the
end of the week. While Granik did not rule out that possibility.
He said: "That would be extreme. We will only cancel things as
we absulutely have to."
</P>
<P>
Training camps are scheduled to open on October 6, and the
first preseason games are slated for October 13. An exhibition
game in Israel between the Miami Heat and Maccabi Tel Aviv, an
international club power, was cancelled earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
The Washington Wizards are scheduled to begin their preseason
with home games on October 16 against the Boston Celtics in
Baltimore and on October 17 against the Philadelphia 76ers at MCI
center in Washington.
</P>
<P>
"I can't talk about that," Wozards General Manager Wes Unseld
said yesterdy. "As long as it's lockout issue, I can't talk about
it."
</P>
<P>
Granik said at least the first week of preseason games would
be cancelled today.
</P>
<P>
"There is no chance we can hope to be ready to play any
exhibition games in the first half of October, and we might as
well let our fans and promoters know that," Granik said.
</P>
<P>
With the regular season scheduled to open on November 3, it is
increasingly likely that it won't start on time. Negotiations
are stalled and Commissioner David Stern said before the lockout
that a month might be needed after an agreement for an
abbreviated free agency signing period and training camp before
games could begin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
