<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Coco Cola Company Remains Operational in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 24 (Xinhua)--The U.S.Coca Cola Company will
remain operational in Zambia despite the controversial excise
duty, said the company here Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The company said it will contine to produce soft drinks in the
country but it is concerned about the government inability to
honor its promise to reduce the excise duty from 25 percent to
five percent.
</P>
<P>
But it expressed its confidence that the Zambian government
will settle the dispute.
</P>
<P>
In May this year, the government promised to reduce duty on
Coca Cola.
</P>
<P>
The company increased two weeks ago the price of its products
from 500 to 900 Kwacha per bottle, the price increase has
inevitably slumped the demand for the products while retailers in
some border areas have started importing soft drinks from
neighboring countries. Last week, the company suspened its
production and threatened to pull out of Zambia.
</P>
<P>
But some Zambian government officials have branded the company
as a black-mailer which has for a long time been evading taxes.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
