<HEADLINE> Chinese Purchase Delegation Visits Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese government
delegation left here Thursday, winding up a fruitful purchase
tour to Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese purchase delegation has signed an agreement with
Nigeria on the purchase of 1,000 tons of cocoa beans and 5,000
tons of natural rubber, the team leader said before leaving for
Cote d'Iovire and Algeria.
</P>
<P>
The 8-member delegation led by Zhang Yuzhen, Deputy
Director-General of Department of Policy and Development of the
Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation, arrived in
Lagos Monday.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting in capital Abuja Tuesday with Nigerian
Agriculture Minister Alhaji Alfa Wali, Zhang Yuzhen said that the
purchase of Nigerian goods is part of the efforts made by the
Chinese side to balance the bilateral trade between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
Wali expressed the hope that mutual cooperation should be
strengthened in the field of processing of agricultural produce
and assembling of agricultural machinery.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the bilateral trade between Nigeria and China
has grown tremendously, increasing from 178 million U.S. Dollars
in 1996 to 327 million Dollars last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
